16/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Parliament on Thursday (15 April) passed a bill establishing stricter regulations on child adoption. 
The government said the amendments were made in line with international conventions. 
The new legislation sets forth separate procedures for domestic and international adoptions, favouring the former.
In other news, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro agreed Thursday to extend the existing visa regime until 1 July. 
In the meantime, they will work on a new visa agreement. 
(Mediafax, Rompres - 15/04/04)
